<h2 id="May2021Conference">May 2021 Online Conference</h2>
     <p>Due to ‘Convid-19 restrictions’, the May 2021 Conference was held on-line, over two sessions, on afternoon of <strong>22 May 2021</strong> and the morning of <strong>29 May 2021.</strong> <mark> to be expanded. </mark> </p>
     <hr class="rule rule--ornament" />
    <h2 id="kathrynStreatfieldAppointed">Kathryn Streatfield was appointed as a Trustee</h2>
    <p>On <strong>14 November 2020</strong>, Kathryn Streatfield was appointed as a Trustee of Free UK Genealogy. Kathryn has a special responsibility for fundraising. She is working with a small group of other Trustees, a member of the Advisory Board, and staff members to identify funding needs and opportunities.</p>

    <h2 id="Scan2100million"> <em>Scan2</em> syndicate, uploads 100 million records</h2>
    <p> <strong>On 13 November 2020</strong>, the <em>Scan2</em> Syndicate reached a significant milestone, with its <strong>100 millionth</strong> record uploaded to the FreeBMD database on this day. Scan2 is one of FreeBMD’s larger syndicates, with over 2,800 ‘all-time’ transcribers from around the world, although many are no longer active. It was founded in 1999 by (the now ‘late’) Derek C Hopkins, who was originally from England, but spent most of his life in Montreal, Canada. <mark>Should the founder be named using the style: Derek C Hopkins (R.I.P) ? - PC.</mark> </p> 
   
    <h2 id="JamesKillockResigned">James Killock resigned as a Trustee</h2>
    <p>On <strong>18 May 2020</strong>, James Killock resigned as a Trustee of Free UK Genealogy. Jim is the Executive Director of the <a href="https://www.openrightsgroup.org/" target="_blank">Open Rights Group (opens in a new tab)</a>, and he has helped Free UK Genealogy especially in the area of Open Data.</p>

    <h2 id="FreeBMDmovesTogroupsIo">FreeBMD discussion groups moved to groups.io</h2>
    <mark> We don't appear to have a page for this topic that I can link to, so adding details here. - PC. </mark>
    <p>In Spring 2020, following the closure of Rootsweb, all four FreeBMD discussion groups were successfully moved to groups.io. We have the main FreeBMD news group; one dedicated group for Syndicate Leaders; a FreeBMD Advice group and a FreeBMD Discuss group. More details, <a href="https://www.freebmd.org.uk/lists.shtml" target="_blank"> including how to sign up, can be found on the old FreeBMD website (opens in a new Tab).</a> </p>
     
    <hr class="rule rule--ornament" />
    <h2 id="20yearsBMD">‘FreeBMD@20’ — Celebrating 20 years of FreeBMD</h2>
    <p>On <strong>Saturday 15 September 2018</strong>, the Free UK GEN 2018 meeting was held at the National Archives, Kew. Its theme was “<em>FreeBMD@20” Celebrating 20 years of FreeBMD</em>. The meeting was free, but attendance needed to be pre-booked.</p>
    
    <p>Our speakers were Pat Reynolds, Graham Hart and Alexandra Eveleigh, from Free UK Genealogy; Audrey Collins, from The National Archives; and Else Churchill, from the Society of Genealogists. You can find a copy of the <a href="https://www.freeukgenealogy.org.uk/news/2018/09/" target="_blank">calling notice on the Free UK Genealogy website (opens in a new Tab)</a>. This event was recorded for those who could not attend in person. <mark>add link to youtube - PC.</mark> </p>
    
    <h2 id="post-1983Records">Preparations for transcribing post-1983 records</h2>
    <p> <mark>To be expanded. - PC. </mark> </p>
    <p>During the <strong>September datebase update</strong>, various files were upload to FreeBMD to enable the transcription of post-1983 records. These included a new version of WinBMD, Version 9.5. These post-1983 GRO Indexes have a new format. They are prepared annually rather than quarterly; and they include a new field — the Registration Date — which gives the month of registration.</p>                            
    <p>A new version of the Registration Districts file, covering the period 1984 to 1992, was also uploaded. This file was produced to acccommodate the various name-changes to Registration District names — often the name of local authorities — that took place in this period.</p>
    <p>Those transcribers who suscribe were notified, via various FreeBMD news groups hosted on RootsWeb, that this new Version of WinBMD was now available for download. Transcribers, on downloading this file to their computer and running it for the first time, would cause the new Registration District file to be automatically downloaded to their computer.</p>
    <h2>July 2018</h2>
    <mark>Check this time frame in respect of 1984 and later records. These 1984 and later records seem to have been started either side of Christmas 2018; and there was a lot of work needed before we could start. I think we were coming to the end of 1983 records. - PC.</mark> 
