    <h2 id="freeUKGEN2017">Free UKGEN 2017 meeting — ‘Community Benefits’</h2>
    <p> On <strong>Saturday, 9 September 2017</strong>, the Free UKGEN 2017 meeting was held in Nottingham, at the Natural Justice Museum. Its theme was “Community Benefits (FreeBMD Volunteers)" with Nick Barratt as our guest speaker. The meeting was free, advertised via FreeUK Genealogy newsletters, but attendance needed to be pre-booked. The event was recorded for those who could not attend. <mark> add link to youtube - PC.</mark> </p>

    <h2 id="GiorgioAbrainiAppointed">Giorgio Abraini was appointed as a Trustee</h2>
    <p>On <strong>7 September 2017</strong>, Giorgio Abraini was appointed as a Trustee of Free UK Genealogy. He was appointed after the Trustees had identified a need to improve the financial expertise of the board.</p>

    <h2 id="FreeUKGenCIO">Free UK Genealogy becomes a CIO</h2>
    <p>On <strong>1 January 2017</strong>, Free UK Genealogy began to operate as a Charitable Incorporated Organization. Notice of this intended change <a href="#intention-CIO">was given in Free UK Genealogy <em>News</em> in November 2015</a>. <mark> Being expanded - PC. </mark> </p>
   
    <hr class="rule rule--ornament" />
     <h2 id="MacBMD-X">MacBMD-X transcribing tool</h2>
    <p>The <strong>July 2016</strong> <em>Free UK Genealogy Newsletter</em> announced the availability of a new transcribing tool for Mac users — MacBMD-X. It is stated to work with all latest Mac Operating systems; and can be download from the <a href="https://www.freebmd.org.uk/addons/" target="_blank"> Transcription Software and Add-ons page on the old FreeBMD website (opens in a new Tab).</a> It replaces and older and now unsupported version — MacBMD. The original version, written by Peter Hines, works only on Mac Operating System version 10.6 (“Snow Leopard”), or earlier versions.</p>
 
