    <h2 id="intention-CIO">Intention to make Free UK Genealogy a Charitable Incorporated Organisation</h2>
    <p>On <strong>30th November 2015</strong>, Pat Reynolds gave notification of the intended change, to make Free UK Genealogy a Charitable Incorporated Organisation (CIO). Notice of this intention was given in a <em>Free UK Genealogy News</em> an article entitled: <a href="https://www.freeukgenealogy.org.uk/news/2015/11/" target="_blank">News: “Free UK Genealogy is becoming a Charitable Incorporated Organisation” (page opens in a new Tab)</a>, dated 30th November 2015.</p>
  
    <h2 id="billyDaviesTrustee">Billy Davis was appointed as a Trustee</h2>
   <p> The same newsletter <a href="https://www.freeukgenealogy.org.uk/news/2015/11/" target="_blank">News: “Free UK Genealogy is becoming a Charitable Incorporated Organisation” (page opens in a new Tab)</a>, included an annnouncement that Billy Davis was appointed as a Trustee for Free UK Genealogy.</p>
   <p>Billy brings with him significant experience in public affairs - having worked both for consultancies as well as “in house” at several NGOs. He has a strong personal interest in genealogy.</p>

     <h2 id="correctionReportingSystem">An automatic correction reporting system for FreeBMD</h2>
    <p>On <strong>10 June 2015</strong>, an automatic correction reporting system for FreeBMD was brought into service. The system assigns ‘ownership’ of incoming correction requests after taking into account: whether transcribers accept, or do not, accept correction requests; whether the transcriber is active or not; and, the configuration set by syndicate leaders for dealing with corrections within their syndicate.</p> 
    <p>It replaces a manual system which had been run for a number of years by the Corrections Co-ordinator. He, was typically managing some 5,000 requests per month, using a spreadsheet running on a home computer, as well as being a FreeBMD Syndicate Leader and carrying out other duties for FreeBMD. <mark> Should the (late) Corrections Co-ordinator be named? </mark> </p>

    <h2 id="PatAppointed">Pat Reynolds was appointed as Executive Director of Free UK Genealogy</h2>
    <p>On <strong>5 Jun 2015</strong>, the Trustees were pleased to report that Pat Reynolds has been appointed as the new Executive Director of Free UK Genealogy. Pat had previously led the Surrey History Centre and other aspects of heritage in Surrey. More recently she had been the first employee of a small charity, the Heritage Crafts Association.</p>

    <h2 id="richardLightappointed">Richard Light was appointed as a Trustee</h2>
    <p>On <strong>April 2015</strong>, Richard Light appointed a Trustee of Free UK Genealogy. Richard has a background in museum documentation (he is the developer behinds the MODES database) and has an interest in linked data.</p>

